      "comment": "FAT FREDDY (1) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at this track over 520m behind Bandit Alex (30.56) in a Grade 5. Should be very hard to beat this time. JIGSAW BILLY (7) drew a squeeze box and was game in defeat when a close second, half a length from the winner Gravel Dust (30.04) at Richmond. Expected to be in the finish again. PROWESS (2) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing fifth (30.58) in a Grade 5 at this track. Solid record here winning two races. Cannot be underestimated. ZIPPING CHICAGO (8) can measure up with the right run.",
